The Cyclo ecosystem is designed to create a self-regulating economic model by leveraging competing incentives, resulting in cyclical price movements.

- **Price Closer to $1:** When the cysFLR price is near $1, new mints are incentivized, increasing leverage by depositing FLR. This can further increase leverage by looping mints (selling minted cysFLR for more FLR and then depositing the new FLR to mint more cysFLR), applying downward pressure on cysFLR price.
- **Price Approaching $0:** As cysFLR approaches $0, Receipt holders are incentivized to buy back cysFLR cheaply and burn it to unlock their originally deposited FLR.  At the same time, the leverage achieved by new mints decreases because of the lower cysFLR price, which means there is also less cysFLR being minted. Together these apply upward pressure on the price of cysFLR.

