### Price Ceiling for cysFLR
The cysFLR price is inherently capped at $1 due to the minting process. If the cysFLR price exceeds $1, arbitrage opportunities will drive the price back down to $1.

For example, if the cysFLR price were to ever exceed $1, anyone could immediately deposit X FLR to mint Y cysFLR and sell the minted cysFLR for more than X FLR, causing an economic infinite loop until the cysFLR price dropped back to $1.

### Floor Price Mechanism
While cysFLR's price could theoretically approach zero, a natural equilibrium above zero will emerge in practice. Users buying back cysFLR at lower prices to redeem their FLR will create demand and support its price.

### Impact of Liquidity
Higher liquidity in the cysFLR/FLR pair on exchanges allows for greater supply, as each mint/burn will have a smaller impact on the cysFLR price.